---
description: Filament v3.2 rules for Resources, Forms, Tables, Widgets and Actions
globs:
  - app/Filament/**/*.php
---

## Resources
- Generate smoke tests for every Resource; when changing a Resource, run tests (add them if missing) and fix resource/tests until they pass
- No View page or Infolist unless requested
- Use `Resource::getUrl('index')` with the exact Resource class (e.g. `TransactionResource::getUrl('index')`), not `route()` or `getResource()`
- Override `getEloquentQuery()` for global scoping (e.g. multi-tenancy)
- Use `->relationship()` on Select for BelongsToMany with `->multiple()` and `->preload()`

## Forms (v3)
- Use `Forms\Components\Section::make()` to group related fields
- Use `->form()` on Actions/Filters (this is v3 syntax)
- Use `->mutateFormDataUsing()` for data manipulation before save
- Use `->createOptionForm()` on Select to allow inline creation of related models
- Use `->createOptionUsing()` for custom creation logic
- `Placeholder::make()` is valid in v3

## Tables (v3)
- Use `->badge()` on TextColumn for status/type indicators
- Use `->color(fn)`, `->icon(fn)`, `->formatStateUsing(fn)` with closures and `match` expressions
- Use `->money('USD')` for currency columns
- Use `SelectFilter` for enum/option filtering, `Filter` with custom `->form()` for date ranges

## Enums
- Consider using PHP Enums with `HasLabel`, `HasColor`, `HasIcon` interfaces for model fields
- Use exact return types from interface definitions
- Never add `->value` when defining a default with enum

## Widgets (v3)
- Use `StatsOverviewWidget` with `Stat::make()` for dashboard metrics
- Use `ChartWidget` for line/bar charts
- Override `canView()` to control widget visibility per user role

## Testing
- Use `Livewire::test(class)` syntax, not `livewire(class)`

## Actions
- Use `->authorize('ability')` on actions for authorization
- For `unique()` validation, specify `->unique(ignoreRecord: true)` on edit forms (required in v3)

## Icons
- Use Heroicon strings (e.g. `'heroicon-o-currency-dollar'`, `'heroicon-m-arrow-trending-up'`)
- Prefix `heroicon-o-` for outline, `heroicon-s-` for solid, `heroicon-m-` for mini
